                  <persName id="t18320906-297-person2450">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WARE
               <interp inst="t18320906-297-person2450" type="surname" value="WARE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-297-person2450" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-297-person2450" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of the Tower. On the 4th of September I was at the corner of Plough-street, in Whitechapel, a quarter before eight o'clock in the evening; I saw a man come round the corner with a hat in his hand - as soon as he saw me he made a stop, and soon after the prisoner came round with this package on his shoulder; I looked in his face, and said, "Ah, Teddy! is it you?" he said he had been employed by a man in the Commercial-road to carry the package, and he was going to take it to the Kent and Essex tavern - I took him to the watch-house, and opened the package, in which I found the bill of parcels.</p>
               <p>
            
